texts.text: *Scream*
I-I shall not forgive this! Never!
Even if I die, the shame you brought me will remain!
I shall never let go of this wrath...
Not until I have my revenge!!
>On an otherworldly mountain—
Have you awoken, Tiamat?
Did you have a nightmare? You were crying out in your sleep.
...I was reliving that day.
The day Marduk and those other despicable gods slew me...!
>Tiamat's rage ripples through the air.
I shall never forget the humiliation I suffered!
Listen well, Marduk and his vile conspirators!
I've returned to kill you all! My wrath burns all the same!
We feel your anger too, but you must be patient for now.
It will take time to locate their whereabouts.
How can I wait?! My rage is unquenchable!
Find them! Leave no stone unturned and bring them to me!
Your efforts will be in vain.
...?! Who are you?
I am from the underworld. I've come to assist you.
The underworld...? Why would you aid us?
I wish to see Marduk's defeat with my own eyes.
Only you can do such a thing, but you must act quickly.
Otherwise, Marduk will be ready for you in the other world.
"The other world"?
There is a world where the Dragon Stream is frayed and volatile.
This world has also been affected,
and the two are now temporarily connected.
Furthermore, I saw it.
Marduk and his godly cohorts are headed to the other world.
Really? But why?
Your rebirth has made it evident.
Although once destroyed, your strength is undeniable.
They'll need to prepare if they hope to defeat you again.
The other world is a perfect place to lie low.
They know their plight and are no doubt plotting against you.
Marduk...
I'll respect your decision, Tiamat.
My mind is set.
I shall venture there and crush them!
Just wait, you damned gods! I'll have YOUR heads next!
>On a mountain outside Tokyo—
Phew, we finally reached the top.
Ugh, that almost killed me! Hiking is torture!
If I'd known, I would've stayed home like Shiang Sun.
Great effort, everyone. I'm impressed.
That was a fine workout. Our muscles must be delighted.
Yeah, it's a nice change of pace.
Whoa! Gotta say, this killer view is worth the pain.
Apparently, this is a notable birdwatching spot.
I brought binoculars. Here you are, [sys user_name].
Thank you.
I don't need them.
Maybe we'll even see a rare species.
You should take them. The difference is like night and day.
Plus, they're vital for reconnaissance and tracking enemies.
Um, we're birdwatching...
...Or we could always just head back...
Huh?
How's your bird trivia, Rika?
I don't know much, but I often shoot airsoft in the mountains.
Well, try to guess what kind of bird I'm looking at right now.
Let's see, it has a bluish chest and an orange head.
Name That Bird!
Orange and blue...
Is it a Japanese robin?
Nope, sorry. Even I know what those are.
I'll give you another hint...
It has a large body...a massive tail...
And a head...huh? What the?!
Of a lion?!
?! Wait, it's...!
C-Coming straight at us?!

*Growl*
*Roar*
A demon?! What's it doing way out here?!
Yo, watch out. We've got more company...!
*Roar*
They ain't the right ones but they sure look tasty!
What's up with these demons...?
Hm? It's Shiang Sun...
You finally picked up. The signal must be terrible out there.
Sorry, but we're kinda busy. Can ya make it quick?
I could say the same. Check this out.
>Shiang Sun sends a video.
...! This is...
Where is he?! Where is Marduk?!
I've come to this world to slaughter you all!
You cannot hide! Tremble in fear as you await the inevitable!
Did you watch the video? It was taken in Odaiba.
The hell...? That big-ass demon is...
She's not alone either.
We're also dealing with a horde of Anzu.
They're giant birds with lion heads.
You mean like the ones here?!
So, they're attacking in swarms.
The other Dx2 branches have sent out reinforcements.
Sorry, but please cut your hike short and return to base.
Gotcha.
Y'all heard him! Sorry, but this trip—
*Roar*

Just turned into another surprise demon hunt!
Devil Download!!
